docs.abstract: In an attempt to better compete with other Grand Slam tournaments, the French Open is renovating and reaching out to young fans, and has increased the prizes.
docs.snippet: In an attempt to better compete with other Grand Slam tournaments, the French Open is renovating and reaching out to young fans, and has increased the prizes.
docs.lead_paragraph: A new era begins for the French Open this month as Roland Garros begins to unveil its renovations and new courts, including the new 5,000-seat arena, named after the French tennis star Simonne Mathieu, which has a semisunken court surrounded by 19th-century greenhouses. A retractable roof is planned for next year.

headline.main: The French Open Spruces Up, and Shows Players the Money
headline.print_headline: Modernizing the Open, and fans’ experience

docs.abstract: Using a quantum computer, physicists successfully reversed time for an artificial atom. You can even try it at home.
docs.snippet: Using a quantum computer, physicists successfully reversed time for an artificial atom. You can even try it at home.
docs.lead_paragraph: In “The Curious Case of Benjamin Button,” a story by F. Scott Fitzgerald and then a movie starring Brad Pitt, a man ages backward: He is born an old man, regresses over the years and dies an infant.

headline.main: For a Split Second, a Quantum Computer Made History Go Backward
